Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *Core Application Developer II* role with *Northwest Bank*. I bring over three years of experience building production backend systems, SQL-heavy data services, workflow orchestration, and support-friendly operational tooling, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I built a *multi-agent* CRM platform with *Python*, *LangGraph*, *LangChain*, and *FastAPI* that routed requests across 40+ sub-agents with tenant-aware access control, requirements-driven application design, and support documentation for faster handoff. I also built a *React Flow* and *TypeScript* workflow editor using *Temporal* for durable execution and resumability, created a *FastMCP* server exposing 160+ backend actions, and added validation, monitoring, architecture diagrams, and data flow diagrams so integrations were easier to troubleshoot and maintain. To keep releases stable, I built GitHub Actions *CI/CD* gates and trace-based evals to standardize *unit testing*, catch regressions before production, and reduce manual reviewer load across 25-30 PRs per week.

At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* with *PostgreSQL* and *Redis* that handled uploads, downloads, and deletions across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO* via expiring signed URLs. I also optimized *PostgreSQL* with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, then exposed the data through interactive *React* visualizations for internal customers and business stakeholders. In addition, I orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions*, reduced *AWS Lambda* timeouts, and improved error recovery across 100K+ weekly executions while strengthening *SDLC* reliability, production support, and operational runbooks. That combination maps well to the mix of coding, troubleshooting, documentation, and change discipline this role requires.

Northwest Bank's mission to empower customers and neighbors with the knowledge and tools they need to improve their financial well-being, together with its focus on *integrity, transparency, trust*, and *collaboration*, matches how I like to work. I value the mentorship aspect of this position as well, and I would bring a habit of building reusable documentation, stable release practices, and clear handoffs that help the broader team move faster and support business users well.

I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my background can contribute to *Northwest Bank* and *this team and its mission*. Thank you for your time and consideration. I can be reached at #ph or #eml.

